abstract: The growing extremism of the debate alienates many people on the left and right.
snippet: The growing extremism of the debate alienates many people on the left and right.
lead_paragraph: Where will abortion opponents stand in 2020? President Trump recently made his bid for their votes, becoming the first president to speak in person at the annual March for Life in Washington, an event held since 1974. Two days later, a Democratic presidential hopeful, Pete Buttigieg, told a woman who called herself a “proud pro-life Democrat” that he would not support more moderate abortion language in the Democratic National Committee platform — basically suggesting that, on this issue, she will not find affirmation or support from her party.

abstract: We refuse to talk about how his failure to deliver major changes may have fed voter disaffection in 2016.
snippet: We refuse to talk about how his failure to deliver major changes may have fed voter disaffection in 2016.
lead_paragraph: The sting of Hillary Clinton’s defeat in 2016 still hangs heavy over the Democratic Party. There has yet to emerge a consensus understanding of the party’s failure to beat an opponent who almost everyone assumed could be defeated. Some have focused on voter suppression, others on Russian interference. Mrs. Clinton continues to blame Bernie Sanders. But missing from the various theories is how Barack Obama’s tenure may also have contributed to voter disaffection because he failed to bring about the transformational changes he promised.

abstract: Pomp and circumstance, high drama and bored doodling: Here’s a look back, in photos and reporting, on the trial that ends today.
snippet: Pomp and circumstance, high drama and bored doodling: Here’s a look back, in photos and reporting, on the trial that ends today.
lead_paragraph: It took almost three weeks for the third presidential impeachment trial in the nation’s history to snake through the Senate, arriving at the final day of votes that brought a conclusion that from the beginning seemed foregone.

abstract: His placement behind his leading rivals in the caucuses on Monday dealt a damaging blow to his campaign. Some party officials say it was a long time in the works.
snippet: His placement behind his leading rivals in the caucuses on Monday dealt a damaging blow to his campaign. Some party officials say it was a long time in the works.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Maybe it was the threat of bad weather. Maybe it was a seating assignment debacle. Maybe it was a struggling campaign organization that still hadn’t found its footing.
